# GEM Raster (IMG) image data
# Digital Research's Graphics Environment Manager raster format.
# Used on Atari ST and IBM PC GEM Desktop.
# Variants: standard (v1), XIMG (extended with colormap), STTT, TIMG, HYPERPAINT
# Spec: https://www.seasip.info/Gem/ff_img.html
# Netpbm: gemtopnm, ppmtogemimg
#
# Header: BE 16-bit version (1-3), header_size in words (8-9 typical),
# number of planes, pattern length, pixel width/height, image width/height.
# No magic string - detection relies on valid header field combinations.
#
# Note: existing Magdir rules in images file are broken due to offset
# corruption from DEGAS file-size checks at the same nesting level.
# This rule provides independent detection.

# Version 1, header_size 8 (standard GEM Paint) or 9 (Ventura)
0	beshort		0x0001
>2	beshort		>0x0007
>>2	beshort		<0x000A
>>>4	beshort		<9	GEM Image data
!:mime	image/x-gem
!:ext	img

# XIMG extended format (signature at offset 16)
16	string		XIMG\0		GEM XIMG Image data
!:mime	image/x-gem
!:ext	img/ximg

# STTT variant
16	string		STTT\0\x10	GEM STTT Image data
!:mime	image/x-gem
!:ext	img

# TIMG variant
16	string		TIMG\0		GEM TIMG Image data
!:mime	image/x-gem
!:ext	img
